---
title: "General Taylor"
key: F
---

# In 6/8, the beat unit is an eighth note (6 slots per bar).
# Two dotted-quarter chords per bar are written as even-split (no dots needed).
# The cadential figure Bb(quarter) C(eighth) F(dotted quarter) = 2+1+3 eighths,
# written as: Bb . C F . .

[Verse]
| (6/8) F | C F | C F | C |
| Bb | F C | F | Bb . C F . . |

[Chorus]
| (6/8) F Bb | F C | C F | C |
| Bb | F C | F | Bb . C F . . |
